# Mapping Study Toolbox Context

## High-level architecture
- Runtime stack: Node.js + Express + Sequelize + sqlite3.
- API entrypoint: `server.js` (serves static `public/` and mounts `/api` routes).
- UI source code lives in `ui/` (Vue 3 + Vite).
- API routers: `routes/api.js` with handlers in:
  - `routes/records.js`
  - `routes/mappingQuestions.js`
- Data layer: Sequelize models in `models/`, schema history in `migrations/`.
- Packaged UI: static files in `public/` (built from `ui/`).

## UI integration
- Backend contract used by UI is defined in `ui/src/helpers/api.js`.
- API base in UI is hardcoded to `http://localhost:3000/api/`.
- UI dev server is configured to run on `http://localhost:8080`.
- UI production build output goes directly to `public/`.

## Data model snapshot
- `Record`: title/url/author/description/abstract/status/comment, JSON fields (`databases`, `alternateUrls`), `editedBy`, soft delete.
- `Publication`: venue metadata (`name`, `alternateNames`, `jufoLevel`, `database`), soft delete.
- `MappingQuestion`: mapping metadata (`title`, `type`, `position`), soft delete.
- `MappingOption`: option value (`title`, `position`, `color`, `mappingQuestionId`), soft delete.
- `RecordMappingOption`: join table (`recordId`, `mappingQuestionId`, `mappingOptionId`), no paranoid delete.
- `Import`: scraper run metadata (`database`, `total`, `dublicates`, `namesakes`, `query`), soft delete.

## API contracts used by UI
- `GET /api/records` supports `offset`, `limit`, `status`, `search`, and returns `{ count, records }`.
- `PUT /api/records/:id` updates status/comment/editedBy and optionally mapping options.
- `POST /api/records/:recordId/mapping-options` links an option to a record.
- `DELETE /api/records/:recordId/mapping-options/:mappingOptionId` unlinks option.
- `GET /api/mapping-questions` returns `{ count, questions }` ordered by question and option position.
- CRUD routes exist for mapping questions and mapping options.

## Important invariants
- Record status domain: `null | uncertain | excluded | included`.
- Include aliases expected by UI in record payloads: `Publication` and `MappingOptions`.
- Question and option ordering is position-driven.
- Existing migrations represent production history; add new migrations instead of modifying old ones.

## Operational notes
- `db-config.json` is used by runtime model loader (`models/index.js`).
- `config/config.json` is used by sequelize-cli migrations.
- `config/config.example.json` exists, but runtime still needs `db-config.json`.
- `scrapers/` is a git submodule and may be uninitialized in fresh clones.

## Current known constraints
- No automated test suite is defined in this repo.
- `public/` is a packaged build artifact; `ui/` is the primary UI source.
